FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778983452
OL,3,CLabour leadership rivals caught up in
OL,4,Cdebate over EU ties
OL,6,FReform UK, whose leader Nigel Farage
OL,7,Fwas among the most prominent
OL,8,Fsupporters of leaving the EU, won
OL,9,Fevery council ward in the Makerfield
OL,10,Fconstituency in last week's local
OL,11,Felections, securing around half the
OL,12,Fvote, while Labour won only a little
OL,13,Fmore than a quarter.
OL,15,FMr Burnham was asked whether he
OL,16,Fremained in favour of rejoining the EU
OL,17,Fin an interview with ITV News on
OL,18,FSaturday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778983452
OL,3,CLabour leadership rivals caught up in
OL,4,Cdebate over EU ties
OL,6,FHe told the broadcaster: "I've said in
OL,7,Fthe long term there is a case for
OL,8,Fthat, but I'm not advocating that in
OL,9,Fthis by-election.
OL,11,F"In fact, what I am saying is focus
OL,12,Fnow domestically, Britain has got to
OL,13,Ffocus very much on the here and now
OL,14,Fand the issues that are affecting
OL,15,Fpeople."
OL,17,FThe Conservatives hit out at Mr
OL,18,FStreeting's proposals for closer ties
OL,19,Fwith Europe.
OL,26,@nD@ZOUsD@AOUwD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
